## Testing After Migration

### Step 1: Verify Database Schema

```bash
# If using Prisma
pnpm prisma studio

# If using Drizzle
pnpm run db:studio
```

Check that:
- All tables exist
- All columns are present with correct types
- All indexes are created
- Foreign key constraints are correct

### Step 2: Run Database Migrations Test

```bash
# Create a fresh database to verify migration
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost/test_db" pnpm prisma migrate deploy

# Or for Drizzle
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost/test_db" pnpm run db:migrate
```

### Step 3: Update and Run Tests

```bash
# Unit tests
pnpm run test:unit

# Integration tests (these hit the database)
pnpm run test:integration

# All tests
pnpm run test
```

If tests fail, check:
- Database credentials in `.env.test` or test setup
- Mock ORM calls match the new ORM API
- Query builders use new syntax
- Type imports are from correct source

### Step 4: Test Common Operations

Create `test-migration.ts` in your scripts folder:

```typescript
import { db } from '@/lib/db';
import { users, subscriptions } from '@/db/schema'; // Or Prisma import

export async function testMigration() {
  try {
    // Test CREATE
    const user = await db.user.create({ // Or: db.insert(users).values(...)
      data: { email: `test-${Date.now()}@example.com` }
    });
    console.log('✓ CREATE:', user.id);

    // Test READ
    const found = await db.user.findUnique({
      where: { id: user.id }
    });
    console.log('✓ READ:', found?.email);

    // Test UPDATE
    const updated = await db.user.update({
      where: { id: user.id },
      data: { name: 'Test User' }
    });
    console.log('✓ UPDATE:', updated.name);

    // Test DELETE
    await db.user.delete({ where: { id: user.id } });
    console.log('✓ DELETE: Success');

    // Test RELATIONS
    const withRelations = await db.user.findUnique({
      where: { id: user.id },
      include: { subscriptions: true }
    });
    console.log('✓ RELATIONS:', withRelations?.subscriptions.length);

    console.log('\n✓ All tests passed!');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('✗ Migration test failed:', error);
    process.exit(1);
  }
}

testMigration();
```

Run it:
```bash
pnpm tsx scripts/test-migration.ts
```

